## Limitations

The primary limitation of this report is the variability in estimates of modern slavery due to differing definitions and methodologies. Additionally, the clandestine nature of modern slavery means that many cases go unreported, leading to potential underestimation of its prevalence. The lack of recent data from some regions further complicates the assessment of the current state of modern slavery.